
// ======================================================================
// 			COMPILER FOR NANOMORPHO
// ----------------------------------------------------------------------
// This is the released version of the compiler for the NanoMorpho 
// programming language. 
// That simply means the compiler is ready to use out of the box, no need
// to build anything from source.
//
//
// See handbok.pdf for more info on NanoMorpho.
//
//						Andrea Björk Björnsdóttir
//							       April 2016
// ======================================================================

Linux instructions:

Extract folder into desired location. You can then create nanomorpho programs 
(.nm files) under nanomorpho/Workspace. 

To compile them, do

% ./nanomorpho.sh -c <filename>.nm

and run them from the Workspace with

% ./nanomorpho.sh <filename>


If you would like to create a symbolic link from the nanomorpho folder you can do so with

% sudo ln -s Workspace/nanomorpho.sh /usr/local/bin/nanomorpho

and then simply compile and run using:

% nanomorpho -c <filename>.nm
% nanomorpho <filename>

